    <note>Liu(2) Cen [1238] Shu's [1230] grandson and Qinzhi's [3584] son. His uncle Anzhi's [3579] wife was a daughter of Wang(2) Anli [1760]. Anzhi moved from Huzhou to Jiangning with sons and some nephews. In 1161, Cen was brought out of retirement  and given his old office, Vice-president of the Board of Revenue, from which he had been purged by Qin(1) Gui [8008] in 1134 because of his hawkish positions. See acceptance speech in XNYL, 190.21b. Exiled before the end of the year to a temple sinecure. Zhejiang TZ, 124.29b still registers him as a Guian resident. Jiankang zhi, 49.38b; XNYL, 53.19b, 77.11b, 78.3a, 81.7b, 15a, 83.13a, 190.21b, 193.13b, 20b, 195.11b, 15b, 16b-17a; SHY:ZG, 70.52b. CBD, 5, 3848-9.</note>
